This is denoted with NO ELIGIBLE RESPONSES next to the survey question. For some survey questions the number of respondents to a question was too low to provide statistically reliable estimates. When this occurs this is denoted with DATA NOT REPORTED next to the survey question. Notes on Presentation of Survey Estimates The U.S. Government Accountability Office (GAO), an agency of the U.S. Congress, is conducting a study on how local workforce areas guide WIA Adult and Dislocated Worker Program participants toward training for available jobs and potential high-growth occupations. As part of this review, we are conducting a web-based survey of randomly selected Workforce Investment Boards. We will be asking you about how your local area identifies available jobs and potential high-growth occupations so that you can guide participants toward training for such jobs, the resources most useful in doing so, and challenges in guiding participants toward training.
